Project 2: Walmart Sales Exploratory Data Analysis

library(lubridate)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(kableExtra)

Attaching package: kableExtra

The following object is masked from package:dplyr:

    group_rows
df.tr.ini <- read.csv("train_ini.csv")
stores <- length(unique(df.tr.ini$Store))
depts <- length(unique(df.tr.ini$Dept))

test_ini dataset contains 45 stores and there appears to be 81 unique departments.

Lets do a time series plot of a random set of stores.

TimeSeriesSample <- function(n.stores = 20, n.depts = 10) {
  store.arr <- sample(1:stores, n.stores)
  dept.arr  <- sample(1:depts, n.depts)
  df <- filter(df.tr.ini, Store %in% store.arr & Dept %in% dept.arr) %>%
    mutate(Date = as.Date(Date, format = "%Y-%m-%d"))
  
  return(df)
}

Apparently negative values somehow exist for Sales_Weekly. While there seems to be a decent amount of structure in the data, there seems to be some quite extreme values which we might want to clean up.

df.sample <- TimeSeriesSample(20, 10)
df.sample$SD_Combo <- paste(df.sample$Store, "-", (df.sample$Dept))
df.sample <- df.sample %>% 
  group_by(Store, Dept) %>% 
  mutate(Weekly_Sales_Prop = Weekly_Sales / max(Weekly_Sales))

ggplot(data = df.sample, aes(x = Date, y = Weekly_Sales_Prop, color = SD_Combo)) +
  geom_line(size = 0.2) +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, 1))
